metadata.name: Driver
metadata.description:
"Com along!" he said. "I am the Driver."
Niggle stumbled down from the ladder. His favor seem to have come on again, and his head was swimming; he felt cold all over.
"Tolkien? Driver?" he chattered. "Driver  of what?" 
"You and your carriage," said the man. "The carriage was ordered long ago. It has come at last. It's waiting. you start today on your journey, you know." 
"There now!" said the Inspector. "You'll have to go ; but it's a bad way to start on your journey, leaving your job undone. Still, we can at least make some use of this canvas now!"

Tolkien, G.R.R, "Tree and leaf" :107
